der<br>Mistress of Imagination</span><br>  Posts: 306<br> <font color=#660000>(9/26/02 8:26:42 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/fcircleofsistersfrm25.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=302.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Healing Eviah</span><hr size=1> A personal letter arrives to each of the healers of the Circle and Clan.<br>
<br>
<CENTER><TABLE BORDER=0 WIDTH=90% CELLPADDING=20 BACKGROUND="http://www.foxgrovecircle.org/eq/parchment1.jpg"><TR><TD><CENTER><FONT FACE="Garamond" COLOR=502800 SIZE=3><IMG SRC="http://www.foxgrovecircle.org/eq/letterknot1.gif"></CENTER><P><I>To the Shamans and Clerics of the Sisters and Brothers,<br>
<br>
There is need. <br>
<br>
I believe that Sister Eviah is suffering from a rare partial separation of spirit and body. This is something with which I feel I am able to help, but I will need the combined healing energies of the healers of the Circle and Clan to complete this healing safely. <br>
<br>
Having been Shadowlost while in the beginning stages of my Shamanistic training, I am familiar with the symptoms. After conferring with the Shaman guild in Halas, I have confirmed what I had feared. Part of Eviah's spirit still wanders in the other realm. With our help, I believe that I can guide her to that fragment of her spirit so that she can be whole once again.<br>
<br>
She will need to be prepared for this spirit journey. Over the next few days, I will start working with her to prepare her mind for this healing. When she is ready, I propose is that we gather together among the spiritual Kerrans around the Old One's campfire. Eviah must sit facing the campfire with all of us forming a circle around the fire and her. This circle of protection will keep us safe while I guide her through the spirit journey.<br>
<br>
To make this work, I will need Wardenn there to hold her and be her anchor to this world. She will need to have a solid foundation and guiding light to follow once she has found the lost part of her spirit. I can guide her in the spirit realm, but he will need to bring her home. I do not believe she will return to anyone else.<br>
<br>
There is another issue that concerns me. She mentioned having nightmares and that there was a dark man chasing her in her dreams. This dark man could be a very real threat and although we cannot intervene should they face each other while she is on her spirit journey, she will need the combined magics of the clerics and the Shamans to keep her body safe should her spirit self need to battle this dark force.<br>
<br>
Despite the dangers, I believe this spirit journey is necessary to heal Eviah and make her whole in body, mind and spirit. Without this healing, she will continue to spiral into self-destructive dementia and we will lose her forever.<br>
<br>
Healers, I call for your aid. Please respond as soon as you can so that we can prepare. Time grows short. <br>
<br>
With gratitude and hope,<br>
<br>
<IMG SRC="http://www.foxgrovecircle.org/eq/msig2.gif"><br>
