Clan of Brothers</b><BR>
<a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=355380">My Magelo profile</a><br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=20371A><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/ujelineth.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Jelineth</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 38<br> <font color=#660000>(9/27/02 9:25:50 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/fcircleofsistersfrm25.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=302.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Healing Eviah</span><hr size=1> Nature must come into play too dear sister Mira. A body cannot just survive a spiritual and soul cleansing, it must require the nutrients of the earth as well to make the body whole. Combine nature cleansing with the soul cleansing of those sisters of the cloth, and the spiritual cleansing of those sisters in tune with the spirit world, and Eviah should be as good as her lively old self.Please let me know what you feel like I need to do to help. <br>
<br>
While I am young, my services are here to help my dear sister and friend Eviah<br>
<br>
Jelineth<br>
What others may see one is blind to. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=20371A><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/uwardenn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wardenn</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.thesafehouse.org/images/ring20.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 21<br> <font color=#660000>(9/27/02 1:19:34 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/fcircleofsistersfrm25.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=302.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Healing Eviah</span><hr size=1> I leaned back in the chair, both legs tossed up onto the table in my little hutt in Kelethin. Late last night, after finishing my hunting with Eviah, I wandered into the Brothers Hall and seen the note on one of the tables near by. Being curious and even bit nosey, I took up the parchment and began to read. <br>
<br>
As my eyes ran across the words, my heart began to pound in my chest. I had been trying despreatly to heal Eviahs wounds, to cure her plauged soul, only to be rebuffed by the Dark Man that haunted her dreams and turned them into nightmares. Every time she and I had come closer and became happier, things would suddenly go spiraling out of control. Pain, confusion, suffering, hopelessness and anger would take control. After we would argue and Eviah would break down, my heart would tear just abit more each time. I felt guilty, causing this pain for her.<br>
<br>
Softly setting the note back upon the table, I knew that I would do what it took for Eviah to be cured. I would be her pillar of love, life and hope. I nodded to myself, standing. It would have to be done soon, the Dark One was getting closer and I had a sinking feeling that he was right on our door step... <p>Warden Wildrunner
<br>
Scout of Bristlebane
<br>
Clan of Brothers
<br>
"Shadows are our allies, in darkness we find solace." Bikbuz Fizzledirk</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=20371A><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/uvlayefrozenheart.showPublicProfile?language=EN>VlayeFrozenheart</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 21<br> <font color=#660000>(9/29/02 10:56:20 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/fcircleofsistersfrm25.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=302.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Healing Eviah</span><hr size=1> I don't know if I may be allowed to do so, but I still call you all my sister and brothers, the only family I knew. I'll gladly join y' if you'll have me.... <p><Html>
