<br>
  <p><img src=" http://freespace.virgin.net/jay.ashby/xkerysig.bmp"></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=20371A><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/uladykry.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lady Kry</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Initiate Sister </span><br>  Posts: 78<br> <font color=#660000>(9/30/02 8:59:33 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/fcircleofsistersfrm25.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=302.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Healing Eviah</span><hr size=1> Upon reading the letter I pull out some paper I gather some of my papers and head to the Temple of Marr.  There in a small office I scribe two letters, one to Mira and one to Nysa.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> First Letter - which is sent to Mirabor.</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
Dear Sister Mirabor,<br>
<br>
Please let me know what I can do to help.  I have many books on spirituality but I must confess, I have little real experience.  I will seek the wisdom and guidence of Mithaniel Marr this evening on this matter.<br>
<br>
Sincerly,<br>
Krystarn<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=20371A><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub101.ezboard.com/umirabor.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mirabor</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elder<br>Mistress of Imagination</span><br>  Posts: 311<br> <font color=#660000>(9/30/02 3:15:48 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub101.ezboard.com/fcircleofsistersfrm25.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=302.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Healing Eviah</span><hr size=1> Mirabor read the messages of support from her Sisters and Brothers, her face grim but her eyes alight. There is hope! She thinks back to Wardenn's recent message to her that Eviah was getting worse. She knew that the time was fast approaching when they would have to act. <br>
<br>
She stepped outside and gazed at the clear sky. Quickly calculating the phase of the moon, she made a decision. The time for new beginnings was the New Moon. On that night, they would gather. On that night, the Healing would be done.<br>
<br>
((ooc: That makes it Sunday, October 6th. Probably early evening. Kerra Isle [next to Toxxulia Forest] at the campfire.))<br>
